The paper deals with sparsity pattern estimation, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. However, given the focus on statistical estimation and signal processing, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses tradeoffs between the number of measurements, accuracy of estimation, and diversity, which are key topics in machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with sparse signal processing, which falls under cs.SP (Signal Processing). The paper also discusses bounds on estimation, which is a topic in cs.MM (Mathematical Methods) and cs.SI (Systems and Control).
